When is a good time to validate input?
(see Map.parseEdge and Map.parsePoint)

Where should methods be put in a class?
Private helper methods that is only used in another method. Should they be put at the
bottom of the class or right below the related method?
If at the bottom of the class, there could be quite a distance between the usage and the
declaration. If right next to the usage, the public API of the class is visually cluttered
with helper methods.

Checked vs unchecked exceptions (specifically IOException and UncheckedIOException)